<h1>The Sociologist&#8217;s Creed</h1>

<blockquote>
  <p>Men make their own history, but they do not make it as they please; they do not make it under self-selected circumstances, but under circumstances existing already, given and transmitted from the past. The tradition of all dead generations weighs like a nightmare on the brains of the living.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>(Karl Marx, <a href="http://www.marxists.org/archive/marx/works/1852/18th-brumaire/ch01.htm">The Eighteenth Brumaire of Louis Napoleon</a>)</p>


<p><i>You should follow me on twitter <a href="http://twitter.com/aaronsw">here</a>.</i></p>
<p class="posted">January  2, 2007</p>

